content: Hello,all friends.Welcome to Online Renju Class.
Today we will have the first theory lesson in new year.
Before the class ,let's warm our finger.
We will continue learning d8 opening today.
virag, Before, casar, Xespok, mayhem, killer21st, strul, luwenzhe, weigui, renjunewbie, bergamot, nick_hopper, HEX77, yyfcsd, whte, slamduk, sosei, LiuJianping.
We have learned two powerful 5 ,which are they?
Last week ,GGM Lu began the  i9 varient , we will continue it today.
In the last lesson,we draw a conclusion that only 6-g7 is good.
There are two possible 8th moves.Where are they?
Today we will focus on g8,and from the next class on,GGM Lu and YY will teach us i8.
In case of 8-g8, black uses positional style, whereas 8-i8 lets black develop quite active position.
Most player like to play i8,and I can't find many data on g8.
We will research togather, and try to dig something out.
g9 blocks the white line,and at the same time ,creats two pairs.
We know,in the opening ,it is good to creat more pairs .
Can white attack now? Who want to try ,say me.
it's noz me, it's my cat playing :-)
White can't attack,but white will have promising structures below.

The problem of g9 is - despite the temporary activity, black does not have enough material to win with direct development in one area, and it would be also too difficult to go back to positional style and control the whole board structures.
It is much better to create only one pair, and at the same time keep the control over all structures on the board.
So the best move of 9 is g6.
Do most people understand the reason? :)
any one want to try to win?
ando as black and yy as white
17-21 first and then d7 maybe better?
what does it connect to what?
yes, it is good. I am not doubting, just wondering :)
we leave it as our homework
maybe not enough material on the lower side to connect ot
12-f7 and then turn to previous one
white can choose from f7, f9, f10 or h10.
No matter how white defends now, black will win soon.
strul as black,power yy as white

Tommorow at 1 pm. (GMT) the world champion of 1995, Mr. Norihiko Kawamura will teach a lesson in Online Renju Class. All the renjuclass students and visitors are welcome to join this lesson in Virtual Classroom. It is such a wonderful chance to learn renju ideas from such a famous Japanese master.
The procedure of the lesson is as usual. The students should not be late for the lesson. The credit points are awarded for active participation.
We are so thankful to Mr. Kawamura for his kindness to come to teach us!!
